**AERO RECORDS**

Provenarc Group LLC

**COMPREHENSIVE OPERATIONS MANUAL**

Standard Operating Procedures, Workflows, and Quality Standards

Aircraft Records Digitization Services

*Version 1.0 \| February 2026*

*Confidential and Proprietary Information*

Document Purpose and Scope

This Operations Manual serves as the authoritative reference document
for all operational activities conducted by Provenarc Aero Solutions, the operating
name of Provenarc Group LLC. The manual establishes comprehensive
procedures, quality standards, and operational protocols that ensure
consistent service delivery, regulatory compliance, and customer
satisfaction across all aspects of the aircraft records digitization
business.

The manual is structured to support both immediate operational needs
during business launch and long-term operational excellence as the
business scales. Each section provides detailed procedures that can be
extracted and expanded into dedicated Standard Operating Procedures for
specific functional areas.

Intended Audience

This manual is designed for use by the following audiences. The owner
and primary operator of Provenarc Aero Solutions will use this manual as the
definitive operational guide for all business activities. Future
employees or contract workers who may assist with scanning, quality
control, or customer service will reference this manual for training and
operational guidance. Partnership organizations including maintenance
facilities and aircraft brokerages will use relevant sections to
understand service delivery workflows and quality standards. Insurance
providers and regulatory authorities may reference this manual to verify
operational compliance and risk management procedures.

Document Maintenance and Version Control

This operations manual is a living document that will be reviewed and
updated quarterly to reflect operational improvements, regulatory
changes, and business growth. The current version is 1.0, dated February
2026. The next scheduled review is May 2026. All updates will be
documented in a version history log maintained as an appendix to this
manual. When procedures change, affected sections will be updated and
distributed to all relevant personnel and partner organizations.

