SECTION 1: Pre-Launch and Startup Operations

This section documents all procedures required to establish Provenarc Aero Solutions
as a legally compliant, fully operational business entity. The startup
process consists of five major phases spanning legal formation,
insurance procurement, equipment acquisition, software configuration,
and facility preparation. Each phase must be completed in the prescribed
sequence to ensure regulatory compliance and operational readiness. The
estimated timeline from initiation to full operational capability is
approximately thirty to forty-five days, assuming no delays in
third-party approvals or equipment delivery.

1.1 Business Formation and Legal Compliance

Establishing Provenarc Aero Solutions requires completing multiple legal and
regulatory requirements at both state and federal levels. This
subsection provides detailed procedures for each required filing,
including specific forms, fees, timelines, and critical success factors.
All procedures must be completed before conducting any business
operations or accepting customer deposits.

1.1.1 Texas Limited Liability Company Formation

**Objective:** Establish Provenarc Group LLC as a legal business entity
in the State of Texas with authority to conduct business under the
assumed name Provenarc Aero Solutions.

**Legal Authority:** Texas Business Organizations Code, Title 3, Chapter
101 (Limited Liability Companies). The Certificate of Formation is the
foundational legal document that brings the LLC into existence.

**Required Information and Documentation:**

Before beginning the filing process, gather the following information.
The legal name of the entity will be Provenarc Group LLC. This name has
been verified for availability through the Texas Secretary of State name
search function at direct.sos.state.tx.us. The registered agent is the
individual or entity designated to receive official legal correspondence
on behalf of the LLC. For a solo operator, this is typically the
owner\'s legal name and physical street address in Texas. Post office
boxes are not acceptable for registered agent addresses. The principal
office address is the primary business location, which for Provenarc Aero Solutions
is Kerrville, Texas 78028. This can be a residential address if
operating from home initially. The business purpose statement describes
the nature of business activities. The recommended statement is:
\"Aircraft maintenance records digitization, document archiving
services, and related aviation document management services.\" This
broad statement provides flexibility for future service expansion.

**Step-by-Step Filing Procedure:**

-   Access the Texas Secretary of State SOSDirect portal at
    direct.sos.state.tx.us using a computer with reliable internet
    connection and a valid credit card or electronic check payment
    method.

-   Select \'File a Document\' from the main menu, then choose
    \'Domestic Limited Liability Company\' from the entity type dropdown
    menu.

-   Select \'Certificate of Formation (Form 205)\' as the filing type.
    This is the only acceptable form for initial LLC formation in Texas.

-   Enter the desired LLC name exactly as it should appear on official
    documents: Provenarc Group LLC. The system will automatically check
    name availability against existing entities and reserved names in
    the Texas business registry.

-   If the name is available, proceed with the filing. If the name is
    unavailable due to conflict with an existing entity, select an
    alternative name. Do not proceed without confirming availability.

-   Enter registered agent information including legal name and complete
    physical street address including street number, street name, city,
    state, and ZIP code. Verify this information for accuracy as it will
    be used for all official state correspondence including annual
    franchise tax reports and legal service of process.

-   Enter principal office address. This must be a physical address and
    cannot be a post office box. For initial operations, a home office
    address is acceptable.

-   In the \'Purpose\' field, enter the business purpose statement:
    Aircraft maintenance records digitization, document archiving
    services, and related aviation document management services.

-   Select management structure. For a single-member LLC, select
    \'Member-managed\' which provides the owner with direct operational
    control. For multi-member LLCs, consider \'Manager-managed\'
    structure.

-   Review all entered information carefully. Errors in the Certificate
    of Formation require filing an amendment which incurs additional
    fees and processing time.

-   Submit payment of three hundred dollars (\$300.00) via credit card
    or electronic check. The system accepts Visa, Mastercard, American
    Express, and Discover. Electronic checks require routing number and
    account number.

-   Upon successful submission, the system will display a confirmation
    screen with a filing number. Take a screenshot or print this
    confirmation for your records.

-   The Secretary of State will process the filing within one to three
    business days for electronic filings. You will receive an email
    notification when the filing is approved.

-   Once approved, download the certified copy of the Certificate of
    Formation from the SOSDirect portal. This document is your official
    proof of LLC existence and will be required for opening business
    bank accounts, applying for business licenses, and entering into
    contracts.

-   Store the Certificate of Formation in a secure location both as a
    physical printed copy and as a digital PDF file. Make multiple
    backup copies.

**Timeline and Cost Summary:**

Filing fee: Three hundred dollars (\$300.00), non-refundable. Processing
time: One to three business days from electronic submission to approval.
Expedited processing is available for an additional fee but is typically
not necessary. Total time to completion: Three to five calendar days
including submission, processing, and document receipt.

**Critical Success Factors:**

Verify that the registered agent address is correct and will remain
stable for the foreseeable future. Changing the registered agent address
later requires filing Form 401 with the Secretary of State. Ensure the
business purpose statement is broad enough to cover all anticipated
business activities but specific enough to clearly communicate the
nature of operations. Maintain the Certificate of Formation as a
permanent business record, as it will be required for numerous
subsequent business activities including bank account opening, license
applications, and contract negotiations.

1.1.2 Federal Employer Identification Number (EIN) Application

**Objective:** Obtain a Federal Employer Identification Number from the
Internal Revenue Service for use in tax reporting, business banking,
vendor relationships, and all federal regulatory filings.

**Legal Authority:** Internal Revenue Code, Title 26, requires all
business entities to obtain an EIN regardless of whether they have
employees. The EIN is also known as a Federal Tax Identification Number
(FTIN).

**Prerequisites:**

You must have already completed LLC formation with the Texas Secretary
of State and received your Certificate of Formation. You will need the
following information before beginning the EIN application: your Social
Security Number as the responsible party, the LLC legal name exactly as
it appears on the Certificate of Formation, the LLC formation date, the
principal business address, the primary business activity description,
and the estimated number of employees within the first twelve months
(enter zero for solo operation).

**Step-by-Step Application Procedure:**

-   Access the IRS online EIN application at
    www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/apply-for-an-employer-identification-number-ein-online
    during available hours. The application is only available Monday
    through Friday, 7:00 AM to 10:00 PM Eastern Time. The system is not
    available on weekends or federal holidays.

-   Click the \'Apply Online Now\' button to begin a new application
    session. Each application session expires after fifteen minutes of
    inactivity, so have all required information ready before starting.

-   Select the type of entity. Choose \'Limited Liability Company\' from
    the dropdown menu. The system will then ask follow-up questions
    about LLC formation date and state.

-   Enter the LLC legal name exactly as registered with Texas: Ironclad
    Records LLC. Do not include any assumed names or DBAs at this step.

-   When asked about trade names or Doing Business As names, enter
    \'Provenarc Aero Solutions\' as the trade name. This associates the trade name
    with the EIN for tax reporting purposes.

-   Provide information about the responsible party. This is the
    individual who has control over, or entitlement to, the LLC\'s funds
    and assets. For a single-member LLC, this is the owner. Enter your
    legal name, Social Security Number, and address exactly as they
    appear on your Social Security card and current identification.

-   Select the reason for applying. Choose \'Started new business\' from
    the dropdown menu.

-   Enter the date the LLC was formed. This is the date shown on your
    Certificate of Formation from the Texas Secretary of State.

-   Specify the closing month of your accounting year. Most small
    businesses use December 31st (calendar year), but you may select any
    month. This choice affects your tax filing deadlines.

-   Describe the principal business activity. Enter \'Document
    preparation services\' or \'Business support services.\' Then select
    the most specific North American Industry Classification System
    (NAICS) code. The recommended code is 561410 - Document Preparation
    Services.

-   Specify the primary service or product. Enter \'Aircraft maintenance
    records digitization and archiving services.\'

-   Indicate whether you will have employees within the next twelve
    months. For a solo operation, select \'No.\' If you plan to hire
    employees within the year, select \'Yes\' and specify the expected
    number.

-   Answer questions about agricultural, gambling, or alcohol-related
    activities. For Provenarc Aero Solutions, the answers to all these questions
    will be \'No.\'

-   Review all entered information on the summary screen. Verify
    accuracy of all fields before proceeding. Once the EIN is issued,
    certain information cannot be changed without filing formal
    amendments.

-   Submit the completed application. The system will immediately
    generate your nine-digit EIN and display it on the confirmation
    screen.

-   Download Form CP 575 (Notice of EIN Assignment) which serves as your
    official confirmation letter from the IRS. Print multiple copies and
    save the PDF electronically with your other formation documents.

-   Record your EIN in a secure location. You will need this number for
    all tax filings, business banking, vendor applications, and when
    completing Form W-9 requests from clients.

**Timeline and Cost Summary:**

Application fee: Zero dollars. The IRS does not charge any fee for EIN
applications. Be wary of third-party services that charge fees to obtain
EINs on your behalf - this service is always free directly through the
IRS. Processing time: Immediate upon submission. The EIN is generated
and displayed on screen at the conclusion of a successful application
session. Total time to completion: Fifteen to thirty minutes for
application completion plus immediate issuance.

**Common Issues and Troubleshooting:**

If the application system times out before completion, you must start a
new session. Information entered in a timed-out session is not saved. If
you receive an error message stating that the entity already has an EIN,
this indicates a previous EIN application was successfully submitted.
Contact the IRS Business & Specialty Tax Line at 1-800-829-4933 to
retrieve the existing EIN. Do not submit multiple applications as this
creates processing complications.

1.1.3 Texas Sales Tax Permit Registration

**Objective:** Register with the Texas Comptroller of Public Accounts
for sales tax collection authority and obtain a sales tax permit number.
This registration is mandatory before collecting revenue from any Texas
customers.

**Legal Authority:** Texas Tax Code Chapter 151 (Limited Sales, Excise
and Use Tax) requires all businesses selling taxable goods or services
in Texas to hold a valid sales tax permit. Under Texas Comptroller
Publication 94-127, data processing services including document
digitization are subject to sales tax on eighty percent of gross
receipts.

**Tax Calculation Method for Provenarc Aero Solutions:**

The applicable sales tax rate for Kerrville, Texas is approximately 8.25
percent, consisting of 6.25 percent state rate plus 2.0 percent local
rate. However, data processing services are taxed on eighty percent of
the total charge. This creates an effective tax rate of 6.6 percent of
gross revenue (80% × 8.25% = 6.6%). For example, a service fee of one
thousand two hundred fifty dollars results in taxable amount of one
thousand dollars (80% of \$1,250) and sales tax due of eighty-two
dollars and fifty cents (8.25% of \$1,000). The customer pays a total of
one thousand three hundred thirty-two dollars and fifty cents.

**Required Information for Registration:**

Before beginning the registration process, gather your Federal Employer
Identification Number obtained in Section 1.1.2, the Certificate of
Formation from the Texas Secretary of State, the principal business
address in Kerrville, Texas, your personal Social Security Number as the
owner, contact telephone number and email address, estimated monthly
sales revenue (provide a conservative estimate such as five thousand to
ten thousand dollars), and the business start date.

**Step-by-Step Registration Procedure:**

-   Access the Texas Comptroller website at comptroller.texas.gov and
    navigate to the Taxes section.

-   Select \'Sales and Use Tax\' from the available tax types, then
    click \'Get a Permit\' or \'Register for a Sales Tax Permit.\'

-   Create a Webfile account if you do not already have one. Webfile is
    the Texas Comptroller\'s online system for tax registration, filing,
    and payment. You will need to provide an email address and create a
    password that meets security requirements.

-   Once logged into Webfile, select \'Register a New Business\' and
    choose \'Sales and Use Tax Permit\' as the permit type.

-   Complete Form AP-201 (Texas Application for Sales and Use Tax
    Permit) electronically. Enter your Federal EIN when prompted.

-   Specify the LLC legal name: Provenarc Group LLC. Also enter the
    trade name: Provenarc Aero Solutions.

-   Enter the physical business location address in Kerrville. This must
    be a street address, not a post office box.

-   Select the business activity type. Choose \'Business Support
    Services\' or \'Other Professional Services.\' Then specify that the
    business provides data processing and document digitization
    services.

-   Estimate monthly taxable sales. Enter a conservative estimate
    between five thousand and ten thousand dollars. This estimate
    determines your filing frequency but can be adjusted later if actual
    sales differ significantly.

-   Provide ownership information including your name, Social Security
    Number, and percentage of ownership. For a single-member LLC, enter
    100% ownership.

-   Specify the expected business start date. This is typically the date
    you expect to begin accepting customer orders, not necessarily the
    LLC formation date.

-   Review all entered information carefully. Errors in sales tax
    registration can cause complications with filing and remittance
    later.

-   Submit the application electronically. There is no filing fee for
    sales tax permit registration.

-   The system will immediately issue an eleven-digit Texas Sales Tax
    Permit Number upon successful submission. This number begins with
    the digits 32 followed by nine additional digits.

-   Download and print your Sales Tax Permit for display at your
    business location as required by law. Even for a home-based
    business, maintain this document in your business records.

-   Configure your invoicing system to calculate sales tax
    automatically. Set the system to calculate tax on eighty percent of
    the total service charge at the Kerrville rate of 8.25 percent.

**Filing Frequency and Deadlines:**

The Texas Comptroller assigns filing frequency based on estimated tax
liability. If your monthly taxable sales generate more than one thousand
dollars in monthly tax liability, you must file monthly. For Aero
Records with estimated monthly revenue of five thousand to ten thousand
dollars, monthly filing will be required. Monthly returns are due on the
20th day of the month following the reporting period. For example,
January sales tax is due February 20th. If you pay electronically via
Webfile, you may qualify for a discount of 0.5 percent of the tax due.
Returns must be filed even if you had zero sales during the reporting
period. Failure to file results in penalties of five percent of the tax
due plus interest.

1.2 Insurance and Risk Management Setup

Comprehensive insurance coverage is essential before handling any
customer documents or conducting business operations. Provenarc Aero Solutions
requires four distinct insurance policies that work together to provide
complete protection against operational risks, professional liability,
customer property damage, and data security incidents. This section
documents the coverage requirements, procurement procedures, and cost
expectations for each required policy type.

1.2.1 Business Owner\'s Policy Procurement

**Coverage Objective:** Obtain comprehensive general liability and
business property insurance through a Business Owner\'s Policy, which
bundles multiple coverage types into a single policy at a lower cost
than purchasing coverages separately.

**Required Coverage Components:**

A Business Owner\'s Policy for Provenarc Aero Solutions must include the following
coverage components. General Liability coverage protects against
third-party bodily injury claims, property damage claims, personal
injury claims including libel or slander, and advertising injury claims.
The minimum acceptable coverage limit is one million dollars per
occurrence with a two million dollar aggregate limit. Business Personal
Property coverage protects owned equipment including scanners,
computers, networking equipment, furniture, and supplies against theft,
fire, water damage, vandalism, and other covered perils. The minimum
coverage limit should be twenty-five thousand dollars, sufficient to
replace all essential equipment. Business Interruption coverage provides
income replacement if operations are suspended due to a covered loss
such as fire or equipment failure. This coverage is optional but
recommended, especially after significant equipment investment.

**Procurement Procedure:**

-   Request quotes from multiple insurance providers. Recommended
    providers include The Hartford, Hiscox, Insureon, and local Texas
    commercial insurance agents. Request quotes from at least three
    providers to compare coverage and pricing.

-   When requesting quotes, provide accurate business information
    including the business legal name (Provenarc Group LLC), trade name
    (Provenarc Aero Solutions), Federal EIN, business address, and detailed
    description of business operations.

-   Describe the business activity as: Professional document scanning
    and digitization services specializing in aircraft maintenance
    records. This service involves visiting client locations to collect
    irreplaceable documents, transporting documents to a secure facility
    for scanning, and returning documents to clients.

-   Specify the NAICS code 561410 (Document Preparation Services) which
    determines the industry classification for rating purposes.

-   Disclose estimated annual revenue. For a startup operation, provide
    a conservative estimate of one hundred thousand to one hundred fifty
    thousand dollars for Year 1.

-   Request quotes for the specific coverage limits: one million dollars
    per occurrence, two million dollars aggregate for General Liability,
    and twenty-five thousand dollars for Business Personal Property.

-   Compare quotes on total annual premium, deductible amounts, specific
    exclusions, coverage territory, and additional insured provisions.
    Do not select coverage based solely on price. Evaluate the financial
    strength rating of each carrier using AM Best ratings. Select
    carriers with an A- rating or better.

-   Review policy exclusions carefully. Standard Business Owner\'s
    Policies exclude professional liability, cyber liability, and
    bailee\'s customer coverage. These exclusions are acceptable as
    these coverages will be obtained through separate policies.

-   Once you select a provider, complete the application form with
    complete accuracy. Misrepresentations on insurance applications can
    void coverage.

-   Pay the annual premium or arrange payment plan if available. Most
    carriers offer quarterly payment plans with a small additional fee.

-   Receive and review the policy documents upon issuance. Verify that
    all coverage limits, deductibles, and business information are
    correct.

-   Maintain proof of insurance in both digital and physical formats.
    You will need to provide certificates of insurance to certain
    clients and partner organizations.

**Cost Expectations:**

Based on industry averages for document services businesses in Texas,
the estimated annual premium for a Business Owner\'s Policy with the
specified coverage limits is six hundred eighty-four dollars. This
amount may vary based on specific business location, detailed risk
assessment, claims history, and carrier underwriting guidelines. Request
actual quotes for binding cost information.

